rlesung über Quantentheorie. Dabei werden die Grundlagen der Quantentheorie, darunter der quantenmechanische Messprozess, der mathematische Formalismus und die Bell’schen Ungleichungen ausführlich behandelt. Auch moderne Konzepte wie das Feynman’sche Pfadintegral werden berücksichtigt. Die dritte Auflage wurde um zahlreiche Übungsaufgaben ergänzt.  aThis textbook for physics students reflects the material in a two-semester course on quantum theory. It presents the fundamentals of quantum theory, including a detailed consideration of the quantum mechanical measurement process, the mathematic formalism, and Bell’s inequalities. It also covers modern concepts, such as Feynman’s path integral. The 3rd edition has been supplemented with practice exercises.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 4aQuantenphysik. 4aQuantentheorie. 7aSCIENCE / Physics / Quantum Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Physics, Chemistry, Mat.Sc, Geosc 2020z9783110704556oZDB-23-DPC0 cEPUBz97831104800090 cprintz978311047995940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311047996640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110479966423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110479966/original  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DPCb2020